        "content": [
          "ITALIAN HAS TWO 'YOUS':",
          "",
          "   TU  = informal (friends, family)",
          "   LEI = formal (strangers, elders,",
          "                 professionals)",
          "",
          "LEI uses 3rd PERSON SINGULAR forms:",
          "   (tu) parli italiano?  — informal",
          "   (Lei) parla italiano? — formal",
          "",
          "NOTE: 'Lei' (capital) = formal you.",
          "      'lei' (lowercase) = she.",
          "",
          "WHEN TO USE LEI:",
          "   - dottoressa, professore, signore",
          "   - hotel, restaurant, shop staff",
          "   - taxi drivers, customer service",
          "   - any first encounter with adults"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lezione quindici"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "LEI PRONOUN FORMS (with capital):",
          "",
          "DIRECT OBJECT:    La",
          "   La invito a cena = I invite you",
          "INDIRECT OBJECT:  Le",
          "   Le mando un messaggio = I send you",
          "POSSESSIVE:       Suo / Sua / Suoi / Sue",
          "   il Suo libro = your book",
          "",
          "POLITE REQUESTS use Lei + verb:",
          "   mi può dire... = could you tell me",
          "   mi scusi = excuse me",
          "   per favore = please",
          "",
          "PLURAL: use VOI (informal & formal,",
          "mostly the same plural).",
          "",
          "SHIFT TO INFORMAL: 'ci diamo del tu?'"
        ]
      }
    ]
